this period due to excess academic stress and fear of failure in examinations resulting from an
inability to attend online classes (Banerjie, 2020; Koshy, 2020). Although the various educational
boards have assured a revised syllabus for the current academic session, increased parental
pressure, limited socialization among peers, physical inactivity, online classes, and various other
underlying reasons may exacerbate academic stress among students. Therefore, this study aims
to understand how the COVID-19 lockdown might be influencing students in terms of academic
pressure and their engagement in coping activities.
Purpose Statement
The purpose of this research project is to investigate the academic stressors affecting
private high school students in India during the COVID-19 lockdown and the coping strategies
engaged by them to alleviate stress. Therefore, this research aims to answer the following
questions:
Which academic stressors, as indicated by stress reactions, are affecting private high
school students in India negatively in terms of mental health and well-being during the
COVID-19 lockdown?
Which coping strategies are practiced by private high school students in India in
response to academic stress during the COVID-19 lockdown?
